records.addlTxt:
State files an Amended Information charging:
Count 1 - Possess oxycodone without a valid prescription, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(am); 
Count 2 - Possess adderall with intent to deliver, contrary to Section 961.41(1m)(b); 
Count 3 - Possess oxycodone without a valid prescription, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(am).
Count 1 and Count 3 - Guilty pleas.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2.   Motion granted.   
Count 1 - Possess oxycodone without a valid prescription - Defendant is sentenced to six (6) months incarceration consecutive to the sentence defendant is presently serving.   
Count 3 - Possess oxycodone without a valid prescription - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation for two (2) years to commence upon defendant's completion of extended supervision in 2024.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
4) AODA assessment and follow through treatment; 
5) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacist unless approved otherwise by the agent; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination; 
9) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.   
Minutes.
